# HFS Copy Video Link Plugin

A plugin for [HFS (HTTP File Server)](https://github.com/rejetto/hfs) that adds a button to copy direct links to video files.

## Features

- Automatically detects video files (mp4, mov, wmv, mkv, avi, flv, webm, m4v)
- Adds a "ðŸ“º Copy" button next to each video file
- Copies the direct video link to clipboard when clicked
- Shows a toast notification confirming the copy action

## Installation

1. Download or clone this repository
2. Copy the `dist` folder contents to your HFS plugins directory
3. Restart HFS or reload plugins
4. The plugin will automatically add copy buttons next to video files

## Usage

When browsing your HFS server, you'll see a "ðŸ“º Copy" button next to video files. Click it to copy the direct link to your clipboard. You can then paste this link into any media player that supports network streams.

